The vertical red arrow in the 240 K data is shown as a guide to the eyes to demonstrate that this
height increases with decreasing temperature. One can clearly notice the change in the peak

, there was only two

peaks below 110 K (see peaks for 100-60 K). With further decrease in temperature (50-6 K), the
intensity of (800) peak becomes less visible because the relative intensity of these peaks increases,
see especially at 20 K. These results infer the change in lattice distortion across the magnetic
transitions and speaks in favor of a magnetoelastic coupling.
